    "title": "Punctuation and Possessives (Hard)",
    "body": "Possession is shown with an apostrophe: add 's to a singular noun, and just an apostrophe after a plural noun ending in -s. A plain -s makes a plural, not a possessive.",
    "key_points": [
      "Singular possessive: add 's.",
      "Plural ending in -s: add only an apostrophe.",
      "No apostrophe makes a noun plural, not possessive."
    ]
